          "title": "Let Them All Talk",
          "year": 2020,
          "note": "Made the bulk of the film during an actual Queen Mary 2 crossing from Brooklyn to Southampton with a roughly 30-person crew; he edited nightly and sent notes to writer Deborah Eisenberg while still shooting."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Good German",
          "year": 2006,
          "note": "He rewatched it recently while thinking about kinship with Fincher's 'Mank'; still stands by it as close to exactly what he intended."
        },
        {
          "title": "Che",
          "year": 2008,
          "note": "Says he's mostly just relieved he finished it."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Underneath",
          "year": 1995,
          "note": "Cites it as the low point that sent him to Richard Lester for advice, which led to 'Schizopolis.'"
        },
        {
          "title": "Schizopolis",
          "year": 1997,
          "note": "Calls it the 'detonation' that blew away the formalism creeping into his work."
        },
        {
          "title": "High Flying Bird",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "Says its Netflix viewership beat likely theatrical numbers by a factor of five to nine."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Laundromat",
          "year": 2019
        },
        {
          "title": "Logan Lucky",
          "year": 2017
        },
        {
          "title": "Out of Sight",
          "year": 1998,
          "note": "Notes it flopped on release but has been retroactively remembered as a hit."
        },
        {
          "title": "Traffic",
          "year": 2000,
